The initial funds will help establish the COVAX facility at an operational level and ensure routine immunisation programmes continue in eligible countries, GAVI said in a statement. In all, 168 countries have joined the COVAX global vaccine facility, led by GAVI and the World Health Organization, including 76 wealthy or self-financing countries, it said. COVAX aims to deliver 2 billion vaccine doses by the end of 2021. --Reuters--